    <string name="instructions_page_title">Facilitator instructions</string>
    <string name="instructions_title">Instructions</string>
    <string name="instructions_subtitle">Read the instructions and recommendations for a successful test.</string>
    <string name="checklist_title">Basic checklist</string>
    <string name="checklist_content">• Check that the device is charged\n• Make sure the environment is quiet\n• Confirm headphones are connected correctly\n• Check ambient noise level before starting\n• Confirm participant data before starting the test</string>
    <string name="doubts_title">Main questions</string>
    <string name="doubts_content">• What is pediatric auditory screening?\nIt is a set of procedures aimed at identifying children with possible hearing alterations requiring diagnostic evaluation.\n\n• How to proceed if the child does not respond?\nRemain calm and try again. If the child continues not responding, note it and refer for specialized evaluation.</string>
    <string name="responsibilities_title">Facilitator responsibilities</string>
    <string name="responsibilities_content">• Ensure guardian consent\n• Maintain the confidentiality of collected data\n• Strictly follow the established protocol\n• Forward results appropriately\n• Record all occurrences during the test</string>

